⸻

Phase 3 — Documentation First
Before implementation the agent:
	•	researches the repository
	•	studies existing architecture
	•	documents requirements
	•	identifies assumptions
	•	defines constraints
Outputs:
	•	requirements
	•	assumptions
	•	implementation notes
Cybernetic principle:
Good Regulator Theorem
Question:
Does building an internal model before acting improve regulation?

⸻

Phase 4 — Planning
Generate a high-level implementation plan.
Each step should include:
	•	objective
	•	expected outcome
	•	affected components
	•	acceptance criteria
	•	proposed tests
The plan becomes the working document for implementation.

⸻

Phase 5 — Step-Level Development Loop
Each implementation step follows the same control loop.
Review current plan

↓

Write failing test

↓

Implement minimum solution

↓

Run tests

↓

Static analysis

↓

