Cybernetic principles:
	•	Negative Feedback
	•	Adaptive Control
Questions:
	•	Does local verification prevent downstream failures?
	•	Does continuous learning improve subsequent implementation?

⸻

Phase 6 — Independent Reviewer
Introduce a second agent whose sole responsibility is evaluation.
The reviewer should inspect:
	•	correctness
	•	architectural consistency
	•	code simplicity
	•	duplication
	•	maintainability
	•	potential regressions
The reviewer should not implement code directly.
The implementation agent remains responsible for repairs.
Cybernetic principle:
Independent Observation
Question:
Does an independent controller detect failures missed by self-review?

⸻

Phase 7 — Whole-System Convergence
Once every implementation step is complete, perform a final system-level loop.
Run:
	•	complete test suite
	•	integration tests
	•	performance benchmarks
	•	architectural review
	•	documentation review
If issues are found:
Identify issue

↓

Repair

↓

Regression tests

↓

Re-evaluate

↓

Repeat until convergence
Cybernetic principle:
Hierarchical Control
Question:
Does global regulation improve overall system quality beyond locally correct implementation?

