Implementation Architecture
The controller will be composed of specialised OpenCode agents.
Initial agent set:
	•	Director
	•	Research
	•	Planner
	•	Builder
	•	Verifier
	•	Reviewer
The Director owns the control loop.
Each specialised agent performs one task before returning control.
This separation allows individual feedback channels to be enabled or disabled without modifying the overall architecture.

⸻

Expected Outcome
The goal of this project is not to build a better coding agent.
The goal is to understand which cybernetic control mechanisms produce measurable improvements in autonomous software engineering.
If successful, the result will be a practical demonstration that agent performance depends not only on model capability, but also on the quality of the feedback systems that surround the model.
